. I got to the point playing my thane that having 2 skalds in groups was something the cherish.  <br><br>I can't count the number of times that I would be standing around while a raid was organizing and raid leaders were making sure that each group had its own Skald. They are a highly prized commodity.  <br><br>Some of my friends in Hib have told me the one thing they hated the most about RvR with Midgard is the Skalds. This was based on two things; 1) skalds appeared to be moving faster than anyone else on the battle field and 2) the ability to root/snare/mez while running full speed. <br><br>As for my own observations after playing 17 levels as a Skald..<br>1) I never have to look hard for a group. Many times higher level groups will invite me to join them just for my particular abilities - speed/BS DD. If I am unable or just don’t want to group – I can solo very effectively.<br>2) The Compell line of spells is a snare and generally doesn't cause aggro. So it seems that frequently I am the puller for the group because I can tag one mob (at respectable range) from a group and not invite aggro. This is really cool.<br>3) Due to my Thane roots, I enjoy the ability to melee as well as do magic damage. Playing a Skald is a very enjoyable pastime. I do not feel &quot;nerfed&quot; or &quot;gimped&quot; in any sort of way. Soloing I can generally kill 2-3 blue mobs or 1 yellow mob before resting. <br><br>If I had to select things to improve the class I would suggest:<br>1) Increase the amount of healing the Rest line of songs does. It's pretty weak right now.<br>2) A Mana and/or End song would be great for groups.<br><br>Oh yeah, is there a Team Thane board someplace?<br><br>Stygian<br>17 Skald Guinivere<br><br><br><br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10