ounds and start killing some albs and Hibs for realm points which in turn give you RA <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Skald Fun) 2) We can't root, and as soon as you cast something on the enemy you slow down.<br><br>No idea where the Thane board is <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Hope I cleared some of your questions and not confused you more <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/EreNi.gif"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvolxwagon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Volxwagon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 12:30:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: General Skald Info and Comments</span><hr size=1> A1) Power for our DDs consumes a large % of our available power pool.  At lvl 40, using both dds typically drops my power bar by about 1/3.  I don't think it's worth rerolling, just realize you will have less DD damage than those that put points into charisma.<br><br>B1) Personally, I have kept BS maxed every lvl from 7 on.  I think it is invaluable to max it for the new shouts and songs.  (Especially if you want to BG - you want the best dds/speed song available).<br><br>B2) You have to RvR and gain what are called &quot;Realm Ability Points.&quot;  You get (1) RA point each time you gain a realm level.  <br>My opinions of the realm abilities you listed:<br>1) Longwind - Definitely get this.  Consider taking to lvl II or III.<br>2) Tireless - Take it to I.<br>3) Regeneration - Not worth getting imo<br>4) Serenity - Possibly worth getting, depending on you RvR style.<br>5) Purge - Get this after you get Ignore Pain.<br>6) Fury of the Gods - In its current state, this RA is laughable at best.<br>7) Ignore Pain - The single most useful realm ability you can get.  This will save you many times over.<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  First Aid - A pre req for IP, so you need it.  If Mythic fixes it (so it does heal the 30% per lvl), it will be a useful pre-req<br><br>Skald Fun:<br>Skalds do not get a root.  The snare is currently broken, and breaks (npi) after the enemy/mob is hit once.  <br>As for the soloing ability...well, this decreases at higher levels.  Once you start taking on mobs that are double hitting and proccing, you feel the pain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=203.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=203.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=203.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.threadControl?topicID=203.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br